abstract: Dutch officials investigating July 2014 Malaysian jetliner crash in Ukraine say they have been blocked from conducting research into Luhansk cellphone towers by pro-Russian separatists who control eastern Ukraine region; investigators were checking Ukrainian intelligence claims that they had intercepted telephone conversations of separatist leaders discussing shooting down plane; separatists strongly deny any involvement in disaster.
lead_paragraph: Pro-Russian separatists, who strongly deny that they had anything to do with the disaster, are concealing cellphone communications, Dutch law enforcement officials say.

headline.main: Dutch Say Separatists in Ukraine Block Inquiry Into Malaysia Jet Crash
headline.print_headline: Dutch Say Malaysia Jet Inquiry Is Blocked in Ukraine
